observationText: The SW1990 cell line was used to establish a gemcitabine-resistant subline called SW1990-GZ by exposing the parental cells to increasing concentrations of gemcitabine over time.
The gemcitabine-resistant SW1990-GZ subline showed significantly lower sensitivity to gemcitabine compared to the parental SW1990 cells in an MTT viability assay.
The SW1990 and SW1990-GZ cell lines exhibited distinct morphologies when observed under a microscope.

The SW1990 cell line showed high expression levels of phosphorylated tyrosine sites on proteins like E-cadherin, DOK1, DLG1, ANXA2, and others compared to some other pancreatic cancer cell lines based on mass spectrometry analysis.
